The architect for this building was Nathan Korn.

718489f-a.title: Manhattan: Central Park West - 77th Street (West)
718489f-a.text:
Central Park West, west side, between West 77th (left) and 81st
(right) Streets, showing there upon, the American Museum of Natural
History. Photographers vantage point is in the Western section of
Central Park and he is viewing due westward to show buildings on the
western confine. This is a set of two views.
February 2, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.

718493f-a.title: Manhattan: Central Park West - 77th Street (West)
718493f-a.text:
Central Park West, west side, south from West 81st to West 77th Streets,
showing the American Museum of Natural History. The center building
(with columns) is the Theodore Roosevelt Memorial erected b the State of
New York in memory of the former Governor of the state and President of
the United States who was a great naturalist and leader in the conservation
movement.
1936.
W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Writers Project.
